projects.name: Synth. Fluorophore-Conjugated Carb. and Developing a Detection Method
projects.description: Plasmodium falciparum is the species of parasite responsible for the most severe malaria cases and can evade immune detection in the placenta of pregnant women by binding to placental cells.  Not much is understood at the molecular level about this binding interaction and we aim to better understand this process and design inhibitors.  The purpose of this project is to design an assay to test potential inhibitors of the binding interaction.  To this end, fluorophore-conjugated ligands are being synthesized to act as reporters in the assay.  Members of a carbohydrate class of molecules have been labeled at the reducing end with the fluorophore 2-aminoacridone and analyzed by HPLC.

data.name: JuBee AndThe MorningAfter
data.bio:
Smooooothness is SO Sponsored by JuBee and The Morning After!!!

Welcome to the electric, soulful, hip-hop smoothness that is JuBee and The Morning After.. About one year ago an MC named JuBee was following his path in search of that mysterious smooth jam. Not knowing what the future held for him he battled through galaxy after galaxy until he came upon a planet known to many as Macon, Georgia. It is here where he soon came across a band of 3 noble hipsters(Alex,Danny,Alec), who were also on the same mission. Together they took on gangs of country music fans and fought their way to the top of Cherry Street Hill. Once they made it to the top there was a loud explosion, and with this explosion came the remarkable power of smoothness and smooth jams...And music as we know it was changed forever with the birth of JuBee and The Morning After....

JuBee and The Morning After is a band composed of JuBee of City Council (Lead Singer) , Alex Scarborough (Drummer) and Danny Davis (Bassist) both formerly of Dope John Paul, eighteen year old prodigy, Alec Stanley (Guitarist) and Matt Sphinx (Synthesizer and Keys) both formerly of The Alec Stanley Seven. These five artist come together each with their own styles and created a electric hybrid sound that is truly invigorating.


    JuBee and Alex met three years ago when JuBee first came to Macon, Georgia. They became good friends and fans of each others music. After a Jam session at Alexs house in June 2010 the decided to collaborate musically. The search for a bassist and guitarist began to complete their band. They didnt have to look far soon after the session Alex introduced JuBee to his fellow band mate Danny Davis who had been working in the hip-hop world making beats in Athens, Georgia. Danny jumped at the chance and added JuBee to the next Dope John Paul show, which unfortunately was Dope John Pauls last show.  Now the trio set out to find a guitarist, they held auditions for their fellow musicians, including Alexs long time family friend Alec Stanley. After hearing Alec and Matt play together for the first time JuBee knew they had to be included in the band. After their first show the excitement finally hit JuBee that he the Morning After would leave their mark in this world. And now JuBee and the Morning After are ion top of the Macon music scene and refuse to stop.
